=head1 DESCRIPTION

These are the details of the specified hypervisor. A hypervisor is
hardware, software, or firmware that creates and manages virtual
machines, and allocates resources to them.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Host => Str

The server host of the hypervisor. This can be either an IP address or
a fully-qualified domain name (FQDN).


=head2 HypervisorArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the hypervisor.


=head2 KmsKeyArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the KMS used to encrypt the
hypervisor.


=head2 LastSuccessfulMetadataSyncTime => Str

This is the time when the most recent successful sync of metadata
occurred.


=head2 LatestMetadataSyncStatus => Str

This is the most recent status for the indicated metadata sync.


=head2 LatestMetadataSyncStatusMessage => Str

This is the most recent status for the indicated metadata sync.


=head2 LogGroupArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the group of gateways within the
requested log.


=head2 Name => Str

This is the name of the specified hypervisor.


=head2 State => Str

This is the current state of the specified hypervisor.

The possible states are C<PENDING>, C<ONLINE>, C<OFFLINE>, or C<ERROR>.



